usiness logic of the application, the view is responsible for displaying the data to the user, and the presenter acts as an intermediary between the model and the view.\n\nThe presenter is the most important component in the Tiny MVP uden compliance pattern. It is responsible for handling user input and updating the view accordingly. It also communicates with the model to retrieve and update the data.\n\nThe Tiny MVP uden compliance pattern is a great choice for developers who want to quickly prototype and test their ideas without having to worry about adhering to a strict pattern. It is also a good choice for developers who want to keep their codebase lightweight and easy", "model_ref": "general", "runner_ref": "llama.cpp", "trace": {"prompt_hash": "1c001bf40921c0aee910fb3c22ea2a1d0d2cb7b0f5668564455cde4c9b0c7035", "purpose": "default", "seed": [REDACTED:phone:41fdea39], "n_predict": 256}}}